    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It looks like we kick off `api.updateEntitlements(ctx)` multiple times at the start of the test.  We do it once when generating the first user (this was added because we sometimes generate a trial license at that time), then send a message on the pubsub, which triggers yet another call to `updateEntitlements()` via the refresh loop.  Then we call it again after adding the license, and again send on the pubsub, which triggers another call.\r\n\r\nSo, at that start of a coderdent test, we call update like 4 times, twice before the license is actually added.  If these race with the 2 additional times after the license is added then we can end up without entitlements at the end.",
